  description: "multiprocessing.pool.IMapIterator class identity — IMapIterator.__name__.__eq__('IMapIterator')==True (len=12, same length as SpawnProcess); IMapIterator.__module__.__eq__('multiprocessing.pool')==True (len=20); IMapIterator.__bases__[0].__name__.__eq__('object')==True (IMapIterator inherits directly from object); IMapIterator.__name__.__len__()==12; IMapIterator.__module__.__len__()==20; contrast: context classes share multiprocessing.context (len=23, longer); IMapIterator is returned by Pool.imap() and Pool.imap_unordered() for lazy iteration over results; verified with Python 3.14.3"
